<br>
High level group for killing the FGs/IGs and other nasty things in the way plus buffs.<br>
<br>
Buffs usually go, 4 crap buffs (pr, dr, cr/fr, see invis), shaman buffs (stam, hos), cleric buffs (aego or hero/ac), chanter buffs (clarity/speed), mr and cr/fr.  Everyone camps as soon as they have all of their buffs and are full mana, logs in an alt and joins the raid channel.  Once everyone has buffs, they log back on.<br>
<br>
Main tank group consisting of a main tank (lvl 52 warrior with the highest possible ac/hps/mr/cr/fr), one bard, one cleric and 3 pallies.  This group goes in first before all others and the main tank starts attacking first.  The paladins take turns using LoH on the main tank so that he does not have to run to clerics for a heal.  They pull the dragon to the back of the lair.  Clerics and casters stay near the bridge/door.  When melees get to 50 percent, they turn off attacks, wait to loose agro if they have it and back slowly to the clerics.  If they have agro and cannot loose it, they stand and die.<br>
<br>
No one is allowed to sit, hehe.  A lot of people on these dragon raids have no clue what they are doing, so be as specific as possible when handing out instructions.  You have to be in melee range in order to land spells.  Make sure casters know that.<br>
<br>
If you are 53+, you will be banished as soon as you are in sight of naggy/vox.  The only exception is if someone else is above you on their agro list.  For corpse runs in the lair, just have a 53+ monk or rogue go in with sneak.  They will not see you if you are not directly in front of them.   If they do see you, you will just get banished instead of dieing.  Having a 55+ mage is good for CoH to get him back from the zone line to the prep room easier.<br>
<br>
High level clerics can help out greatly by running in with the main group and getting off one complete heal before being banished.  If they bind in the prep room before the raid, they can then gate back and get off another few heals.  I did this for vox and it was pretty fun.  By the time I ran in for the 3rd time, all the tanks were dead, hehe.  As long as you do not attack or cast, you will not be banished if there are people in the room under 53.  Might be a good idea to have a shaman go in just after the main group and attempt to slow.  One of my friends had an idea to have a few mana burning wizzies to see if they could kill vox, but it wouldn't work unless you had someone under 53 tanking the dragon first.  Pretty much any caster over 52 can go in and help out to some extent.  Melees just can't stay in the room long enough to cause any real damage.<br>
<br>
A lot of naggy/vox raids will lower the level limit for clerics to 39 because we get complete heal at 39.  This is NOT a good idea.  All casters should be just as high as the melees.  Why?  AE fear is a pain.  Resisting it depends a lot on your level.  At 52+, I almost always resist it from naggy and vox and I have the same MR I had when I was 40ish and on these raids.  Lower level clerics will just get feared and not be able to cast anything or worse fall into the pits.  I was on one vox raid where I was pretty much the only cleric.  There were 3 in the beginning, but one left just before the raid started.  I was lvl 52 and the other one was 42.  I saw the 42 cleric run out feared in the beginning and never saw him again.  That left only the druids and me.  We were lucky to win that time.<br>
<br>
Have someone that knows the way mark it with dropped items like summoned food for vox.  If you loose most of your raid force because they fall into pits, you will fail.  Also, when pulling the terrors, make sure people are not inbetween the terror and the ramp.  They blow you across the room if you have agro and I have seen people knocked up the wrong ramp and into pit.<br>
<br>
For vox, mana sieve is nice, but not completely necessary.  Have everyone carry a shield if not a large race and use bash.  You can switch out weapons once bash pops up if you have good hotkeys.  Also, chain cast stuns on her.  She is immune to the stun effect (does not stop her from hitting), but it will interrupt her spells.<br>
